WorkItem.Description:
Carver.cs appears to have an issue in lines 479-492, specifically:

	if (mesh.behavior.RegionAttrib)
	{
		// Make the triangle's attributes larger.
		double[] attributes = new double[mesh.eextras + 1];

		// Assign every triangle a regional attribute of zero.
		tri.orient = 0;
		foreach (var t in mesh.triangles.Values)
		{
			Array.Copy(tri.triangle.attributes, attributes, mesh.eextras);
			tri.triangle = t;
			tri.triangle.attributes = attributes;
		}
	}

this basically means if you try to fill in the region attributes via code, it always ignores them since RegionAttrib is never set, and if you DO manually set RegionAttrib, it will crash on the Array.Copy due to tri.triangle.attributes not being filled in.

Anyway, this should fix it:

	if (mesh.behavior.RegionAttrib)
	{
		// Assign every triangle a regional attribute of zero.
		foreach (var t in mesh.triangles.Values)
		{
			if( t.attributes == null )
				t.attributes = new double[mesh.eextras+1];
			else
				Array.Resize( ref t.attributes, mesh.eextras+1 );

			t.attributes[ mesh.eextras ] = 0;
		}
	}
